<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="65" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="4.[136,1452,940,1651]" pageId="4" pageNumber="65">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[136,292,940,966]" pageId="4" pageNumber="65">Distribution:</emphasis>
—Eastern 
<collectingCountry box="[415,508,940,966]" name="Georgia" pageId="4" pageNumber="65">Georgia</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[521,622,940,966]" name="Armenia" pageId="4" pageNumber="65">Armenia</collectingCountry>
, north-eastern 
<collectingCountry box="[795,876,940,966]" name="Turkey" pageId="4" pageNumber="65">Turkey</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[889,1012,940,966]" name="Azerbaijan" pageId="4" pageNumber="65">Azerbaijan</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[1075,1124,941,967]" name="Iran" pageId="4" pageNumber="65">Iran</collectingCountry>
. The border line in 
<collectingCountry box="[1362,1452,940,966]" name="Georgia" pageId="4" pageNumber="65">Georgia</collectingCountry>
between this subspecies and the typical plants is almost identical with the border of the “ 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="65">subtropical wet humid zone of the sea”</emphasis>
in the west and the two remaining zones in the east, “ 
<emphasis box="[824,1265,1012,1039]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="65">subtropical climate of the of the sea wet</emphasis>
” and 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="65">“moderate humid subtropical transition to the subtropics of the previous Asian mountain regions”</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Shetekauri, S. &amp; Kuthatheladze, L." pageId="4" pageNumber="65" pagination="38 - 48" refId="ref5118" refString="Shetekauri, S. &amp; Kuthatheladze, L. (2017) Diversity, Ecotopology and Hypsometric Distribution of the Endemic Flora in High-Mountain Phytolandscapes of the Caucasus. Earth Sciences 6 (5 - 1): 38 - 48." type="journal article" year="2017">Shetekauri &amp; Kuthatheladze 2017</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[136,1452,940,1651]" pageId="4" pageNumber="65">
Eponymy:—The name of the subspecies commemorates the collector Johann Friedrich Adam, later called Michael Friedrich Adams (1780 
<collectingRegion box="[403,499,1157,1183]" country="Russia" name="Moscow" pageId="4" pageNumber="65">Moscow</collectingRegion>
– 1838 Vereya).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[136,1452,940,1651]" pageId="4" pageNumber="65">
<bibRefCitation author="Mabberley, D. J." box="[189,434,1192,1219]" pageId="4" pageNumber="65" pagination="65 - 73" refId="ref4653" refString="Mabberley, D. J. (1982) William Roxburgh's Botanical Description of a New Species of Swietenia (Mahogany) and Other Overlooked Binomials in 36 Vascular Plant Families. Taxon 31 (1): 65 - 73. https: // doi. org / 10.2307 / 1220591" type="journal article" year="1982">Mabberley (1982: 69)</bibRefCitation>
pointed at the existence of the name 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Willdenow" authorityYear="1809" box="[846,1027,1192,1218]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Cacalia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="4" pageNumber="65" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pinnata">
<emphasis box="[846,1027,1192,1218]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="65">Cacalia pinnata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the form “ 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Willdenow" authorityYear="1809" box="[1176,1357,1192,1218]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Cacalia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="4" pageNumber="65" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pinnata">
<emphasis box="[1176,1357,1192,1218]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="65">Cacalia pinnata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
[Adams ex] 
<bibCitation author="G. F. Hoffm." box="[184,687,1228,1255]" page="7" pageId="4" pageNumber="65" score="0.0028073001959915225" volumeTitle="Hortus Mosquensis" year="1808">
G.F. Hoffm., 
<bibCitation box="[343,687,1228,1255]" page="7" pageId="4" pageNumber="65" score="0.0028073001959915225" volumeTitle="Hortus Mosquensis" year="1808">Hortus Mosquensis: 7 (1808)</bibCitation>
</bibCitation>
, nom. superfl. for 
<taxonomicName authority="Bieb." authorityName="M. Bieberstein" authorityYear="1808" box="[913,1189,1228,1255]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Senecio" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="4" pageNumber="65" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="othonnae">
<emphasis box="[913,1116,1228,1255]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="65">Senecio othonnae</emphasis>
Bieb.
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName box="[1208,1351,1228,1255]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Compositae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="4" pageNumber="65" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Compositae</taxonomicName>
)ˮ. As he correctly noted, this name was validly published by 
<bibRefCitation author="Hoffmann, G. F." box="[724,920,1264,1291]" pageId="4" pageNumber="65" refId="ref4435" refString="Hoffmann, G. F. (1808) Hortus Mosquensis. Typ. Caes. Univ., Mosqua, 16 pp." type="book" year="1808">Hoffmann (1808)</bibRefCitation>
with a reference to 
<taxonomicName authority="M. Bieb." authorityName="M. Bieberstein" authorityYear="1808" box="[1146,1452,1264,1291]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Senecio" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="4" pageNumber="65" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="othonnae">
<emphasis box="[1146,1344,1264,1291]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="65">Senecio othonnae</emphasis>
M. Bieb.
</taxonomicName>
and is therefore a superfluous illegitimate substitute name. Its resurrection as a subspecies of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="C. A. Meyer" authorityYear="1831" baseAuthorityName="M. Bieb." box="[1229,1451,1300,1326]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Jacobaea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="4" pageNumber="65" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="othonnae">
<emphasis box="[1229,1451,1300,1326]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="65">Jacobaea othonnae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
would be nomenclaturally impossible (ICN Art. 6.3, Note 2; Art. 
<emphasis box="[903,952,1337,1363]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="65">52.1</emphasis>
), therefore a new name should be created. 
<bibRefCitation author="Willdenow, C. L." box="[136,360,1372,1399]" pageId="4" pageNumber="65" refId="ref5472" refString="Willdenow, C. L. (1809) Enumeratio plantarum Horti Regii Berolinensis, continens descriptiones omnium vegetabilium in horto dicto cultorum. In taberna libraria scholae realis, Berlin, 1099 pp. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 165500" type="book" year="1809">Willdenow’s (1809)</bibRefCitation>
later isonym, published only one year later, has a short description in which he does not mention any pubescence of the described plants but clearly refers to the finder “ 
<emphasis box="[962,1267,1408,1434]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="65">detexit celeberimus Adams</emphasis>
”, indicating the collector of Hoffman’s specimen. This must also be disregarded (ICN Art. 6.3, Note 2). As a 
<typeStatus box="[1180,1281,1444,1470]" pageId="4" pageNumber="65">holotype</typeStatus>
, we designated Adams’ specimen in Hoffmann’s collection. Another specimen with the name 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Willdenow" authorityYear="1809" box="[1020,1194,1480,1506]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Cacalia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="4" pageNumber="65" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pinnata">Cacalia pinnata</taxonomicName>
collected by Adams is deposited in Willdenow’s herbarium (
<bibRefCitation author="Ledebour, C. F. von" box="[550,726,1516,1543]" pageId="4" pageNumber="65" pagination="463 - 718" refId="ref4572" refString="Ledebour, C. F. von (1845) Flora Rossica, vol. 2 (2,6). E. Schweizerbart, Stuttgart, pp. 463 - 718. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 6606" type="book chapter" year="1845">Ledebour 1845</bibRefCitation>
): Habitat in alpibus Caucasi; in monte Kaischaur [Kaishaurni, 
<geoCoordinate degrees="42" direction="north" minutes="26" orientation="latitude" pageId="4" pageNumber="65" precision="15" seconds="29" value="42.44139">42° 26’ 29” N</geoCoordinate>
, 
<geoCoordinate box="[264,424,1552,1579]" degrees="44" direction="east" minutes="30" orientation="longitude" pageId="4" pageNumber="65" precision="15" seconds="38" value="44.510555">44° 30’ 38” E</geoCoordinate>
] &amp; Alwart Iberae, B-W 15064-01 1. 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="65">https://plants.jstor.org/stable/10.5555/al.ap.specimen. b%20-w%2015064%20-01%201.</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[136,1452,940,1651]" box="[189,1365,1624,1651]" pageId="4" pageNumber="65">Both specimens were undated but collected in his journeys across Transcaucasia in the years 1800–1802.</paragraph>
